<HEAD>Nearly 2,000 `Batman' Bikes Stolen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARSON, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Detectives are trying to track down the
joker who stole 1,980 ``Batman'' bicycles.
   The bandits took the bikes, worth $90,000, from the Schaefer
Brothers Distribution trucking company last weekend, said Detective
Larry Thompson of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department.
   ``The only thing we know for sure is they cut the locks off the
chain-link gates and went in there with some tractors and stole the
bikes,'' Thompson said Tuesday. ``We have very little to work with
right now.''
   Investigators believe the thieves first stole two big-rig
trailers to haul away the bicycles.
