<HEAD>Aquino Declares State Of Emergency</HEAD>
<UNK>Eds: To ADD that Aquino had turned down previous recommendation to
declare state of emergency, INSERT one graf after 3rd, `It was ...' Picks
up 4th pvs, `The announcement ...'</UNK>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Corazon Aquino on Wednesday
declared a state of national emergency throughout the Philippines.
   Mrs. Aquino issued the proclamation on the sixth day of the most
serious armed bid to topple her nearly 4-year-old government.
   ``Upon my directive, appropriate emergency measures shall
henceforth be strictly carried out by the duly authorized head of
the concerned agency of the government,'' Mrs. Aquino said.
   It was unclear what specific additional powers Mrs. Aquino would
be able to wield under the emergency declaration.
   On Monday, assistant Press Secretary Lourdes Sytangco said Mrs.
Aquino had turned down recommendations from some Cabinet members
that she declare a state of emergency to cope with the military
uprising.
   The announcement came as an estimated 400 rebel soldiers
continued to hold Manila's financial district and another 400 held
a military base on Cebu Island.
   Earlier in the day, the rebels and government forces had agreed
to a temporary cease-fire that allowed hundreds of Americans and
other foreigners to be evacuated from the embattled Makati
financial district.
