<HEAD>New Ambassador Presents Credentials to Ceausescu</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Alan Green Jr., the new U.S. ambassador
to Romania, presented his credentials Wednesday to President
Nicolae Ceausescu, Romanian media reported.
   Ceausescu conveyed his greetings to President Bush and
re-emphasized his policy of rejecting ``all forms of outside
interference'' in Romania's domestic affairs, the offcial Agerpres
news agency reported.
   The United States repeatedly has called on Romania, the only
Soviet bloc country still resistant to political or economic
reforms, to improve its record on human rights.
   Last year, Congress terminated Romania's Most-Favored Nation
trading status. The Ceausescu leadership said it no longer wanted
it, citing alleged interference in its domestic affairs.
