<SECOND>BC-Japan-Oil,0108</SECOND>
<HEAD>Japex Establishes Gulf of Mexico Unit To Explore for Oil</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Japan Petroleum Exploration Co., or Japex, has
established a wholly owned subsidiary to explore for oil and
natural gas in the Gulf of Mexico, company officials said Wednesday.
   The new firm, Japex Gulf Exploration Ltd., will drill six
exploratory wells in conjunction with Japex (U.S.) Corp., a U.S.
unit of Japex. A first wildcat well has been drilled, they said.
   The new company was established in order to secure financing
from Japan National Oil Corp., an independent governmental body for
the promotion of Japanese oil exploration.
</TEXT>
