<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreet2pm     12-06 0383</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 2pm,0401</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were most lower in moderate
afternoon trading today.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was down 6.83 points to
2,734.85 at 2 p.m. EST. The blue-chip indicator was down 3.41
points at noon.
   Declining issues outpaced advancers by a 7 to 6 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, with 756 issues down, 644 up and 538
unchanged.
   Big Board volume came to 106.45 million shares.
   Analysts said banking and technology stocks highlighted selling
activity.
   The government reported today that the nation's commercial banks
lost $744 million in the third quarter this year, due partly to
rising real estate loan problems.
   IBM led technology stocks lower after gains in the previous two
sessions. IBM stock rose Tuesday after the company announced a
major restructuring but traders said investors were selling the
stock amid uncertainty about the impact of the changes.
   Analysts also attributed the market's sluggishness to investor
caution ahead of Friday's unemployment report. Data suggesting a
further slowdown in economic growth likely would be positive for
the market, analysts said, because it would raise expectations that
the Federal Reserve would continue easing interest rates.
   ``There's a lack of direction. People don't know what to do,''
said Hildegarde Zagorski, analyst with Prudential-Bache Securities
Inc. ``They're sitting around waiting for Friday's report.''
   The market generally ignored a government report on
third-quarter productivity and the Fed's ``beige book'' summary of
economic conditions, dealers said.
   The Labor Department reported that productivity in the non-farm
sector of the economy improved at an annual rate of 2.5 percent in
the third quarter while hours worked grew at a slower 1.3 percent,
a sign of slackening demand for goods.
   The Fed report said the nation's economy was ``stable to
modestly expanding.''
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
down 0.50 to 192.69.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index was up
0.55 to 375.43.
   Among actively traded issues on the NYSE, IBM was down 1 to 98|,
First Interstate Bank Corp. was off 1\ to 52, NCNB was down 2\ to
42| and BankAmerica had lost 1] to 26.
   Chevron, meanwhile, was up ~ to 71|, Chrysler had added \ to 19\
and Deere &amp; Co. was up | to 57{.
