said Hildegarde Zagorski, analyst with Prudential-Bache Securities
Inc. ``They're sitting around waiting for Friday's report.''
   Data suggesting a further slowdown in economic growth likely
would be positive for the market, analysts said, because investors
would expect the Federal Reserve to continue easing interest rates
to stimulate the economy.
   A government report on third-quarter productivity and the Fed's
``beige book'' summary of economic conditions, was generally
neutral for the stock market, dealers said.
   However, the bond market, which had been stagnant in recent
sessions, reacted negatively to the Fed report, which said the
nation's economy was ``stable to modestly expanding.'' Traders said
weakness in the credit market was having some impact on the stock
