<FIRST>r f BC-QueenMary-Harrods     12-06 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Queen Mary-Harrods,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Harrods Outlet to Open Aboard Queen Mary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Harrods, the huge London store, will
open its first U.S. retail outlet Jan. 5 aboard the Queen Mary, the
British ocean liner now docked in this seaport as a tourist
attraction.
   The agreement with Harrods, along with a ``Voyage to 1939''
promotion on board the Queen Mary, are part of a strategy to
attract visitors to the ship and the next-door Spruce Goose, Howard
Hughes' huge old ``flying boat.''
   The Harrods outlet will be 900 square feet, less than 1 percent
the size of the department store in London's Knightsbridge section.
   Walt Disney Co. manages the Queen Mary and the Spruce Goose for
the city of Long Beach. Disney also hopes to lure such well-known
British retailers as Crabtree &amp; Evelyn, Burberry, Dunhill, Pringle
and Laura Ashley to the Queen Mary, said Jack Lindquist, a Disney
marketing official.
</TEXT>
